{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489111"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:05:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:05:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"594"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/594"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.74,0.13,0.04,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"594"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104688"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/594"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"594"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"87042"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"108"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"999"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1808"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11413"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37409"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37410"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42105"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43019"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44332"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/104688"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of tingling and burning sensations in his feet and hands. He was diagnosed with tuberculosis and commenced treatment one month ago. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell with a pulse rate of 92/min, blood pressure 125/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 20/min, SpO2 96% on room air, and temperature 37.5\u00b0C. Chest examination reveals crackles in the right upper zone. There is reduced sensation to light touch in a stocking-glove distribution of his hands and feet. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medicines used in the treatment of tuberculosis is most likely to cause the presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Rifampicin","Isoniazid","Pyrazinamide","Ethambutol","Dexamethasone"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has pulmonary tuberculosis with symptoms of peripheral neuropathy, which is a known adverse effect of certain anti-tuberculosis medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIsoniazid\u003C/strong\u003E is most associated with peripheral neuropathy. The drug inhibits pyridoxine phosphokinase, leading to pyridoxine (vitamin B6) deficiency. The resulting peripheral neuropathy typically presents as paresthesia, numbness, and pain in a stocking-glove distribution. Patients on isoniazid should receive pyridoxine supplementation to avoid this adverse effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERifampicin\u003C/strong\u003E commonly causes orange-red discoloration of body fluids (urine, tears, sweat) and can cause hepatotoxicity. It is also a potent inducer of cytochrome P450 enzymes, leading to significant drug interactions with medications such as warfarin. Peripheral neuropathy is not a characteristic adverse effect of rifampicin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPyrazinamide\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily associated with hepatotoxicity and hyperuricemia, which can precipitate gout attacks. It may also cause arthralgias and myalgias. Peripheral neuropathy is not typically seen with pyrazinamide use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEthambutol\u003C/strong\u003E is known for causing optic neuritis, which can lead to decreased visual acuity, altered colour perception (particularly red-green discrimination), and visual field defects. It does not commonly cause peripheral neuropathy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDexamethasone\u003C/strong\u003E is not a standard first-line medication for tuberculosis treatment, though it may be used as an adjunct in tuberculous meningitis or severe pericardial disease. Adverse effects of corticosteroids are numerous, but do not include peripheral neuropathy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Isoniazid can cause peripheral neuropathy due to interference with pyridoxine (vitamin B6) metabolism.","Pyridoxine supplementation is recommended for patients on isoniazid therapy to prevent peripheral neuropathy.","Peripheral neuropathy from isoniazid typically presents as paresthesia, numbness, and pain in a stocking-glove distribution."],"references":["Nahid P, Dorman SE, Alipanah N, et al. Official American Thoracic Society/Centers for Disease Control and Prevention/Infectious Diseases Society of America Clinical Practice Guidelines: Treatment of Drug-Susceptible Tuberculosis. Clinical infectious diseases : an official publication of the Infectious Diseases Society of America. 2016;63:e147-e95.","Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"87042"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"594"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"ty